          "body": "Verse 14's report that 'the LORD exalted Joshua in the sight of all Israel, so that they revered him just as they had revered Moses' is not a biographical footnote — it is the fulfillment of a divine promise made at 3:7 and the completion of a literary-theological pattern. Moses's authority was authenticated by the parting of the Red Sea; Joshua's authority is authenticated by the parting of the Jordan. The same God, the same type of miracle, the same result: a generation of Israelites who recognize and honor their divinely appointed leader. The pattern matters for the rest of Joshua: when Joshua later speaks (chapters 5-12), Israel needs no crisis of confidence. The Jordan established his voice as God's voice to them."
